com.mikehelmick.proc

Class Message

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mikehelmick.proc.Message
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class Message
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Message that is sent from one process to another (or all other) process(es). This framework does NOT interpret the payload (a string) in any way.

    Create messages using the Message.MessageBuilder. When you send a message the sender and receiver are filled in by the message routing code to ensure correctness / to avoid spoofing. A future version may allow for ovrriding of this behavior to allow for greater fault simulation.
